{
  "text": "In the literature, we find six patients with Ollier's disease surgically treated for low-grade (grade I) chondrosarcoma of the distal end of the femur. Four of these patients were reported by Liu et al. [CITATION_1] Treatment consisted of two transfemoral amputations, one coxofemoral disarticulation and one tumor resection. Reconstruction procedures were not specified. Survival was not correlated with surgical procedure, and at the minimum follow-up of 8 years there was a single death, the patient who had undergone amputation.",
  "citation_candidates": [
